title: For Sale:  Colt Trooper MK III .357 CTG Trooper Mark III MKIII w/Original Box!
postcontent:
For sale or trade is a very nice Colt Trooper MK III .357 mag. / .38 revolver with original box, serial number shows 1975 production.  Overall this is a clean revolver in the beautiful deep blue Colt finish.  The finish looks great, but there is a little thinning and wear along the very front edge of the cylinder maybe from resting in a holster at some time, pics may not show it and a touch at the muzzle.  There is a small area on the cylinder where there is/was maybe surface rust?? maybe a 1/8"x1/8" area.  There is a faint drag line on the cylinder, which tells me this one was shot very little.  Other than the areas mentioned, this is a beautiful piece.  Oh, the wood grips look perfect, no scratches or wear anywhere.  The box is in good/descent shape with some wear and someone has put tape on it.  As you can see the foil label is there and in pretty good shape.  Bottom line, the box is not in great condition, but more important, I have it, which is huge when it comes to the overall value.  Let me know if serious and interested in seeing more pics, I have about a dozen or so.

$960 cash obo. Will consider trades around or above the asking price.  The Trooper's have steadily increased in value over the past couple of years, I've seen them for sale in the $600's and up into the thousands, depending on the finish, condition, if the box & ppwk are included etc., so really all over the place as far as value goes.  I'm in no hurry to get rid of this one as these will only increase in value.  If you are looking for an investment piece, this is a sure thing and shooting it will not decrease the value on these, these are tanks.  I also have a very nice Trooper MK III 4" Nickel, I would sell both for $1,700 if someone is interested.

If wanting to trade, please state exactly what you have and exactly what you want to do, straight trade, trade +/- cash, ammo, optics, gold, silver etc. etc., so I know the deal and I will consider. I like a bit of everything.

I'm not in need of anything right now, but I listed some I would not mind having or having more of, but not limited to:

Eotech, maybe Aimpoint and descent magnifier (not Eotech) in the 5x-6x power range.  I am trying to finish off several rifle projects if someone has multiples.
Vepr 7.62x54 or .308 with barrel 20.5"-23", maybe another PSL
Quality uppers in 5.56 or 7.62x39 or a .50 Beowulf would be cool.  
Sig 556 or 556r ( only the newer model with the upgrades and bugs worked out)
Will consider several quality stripped AR lowers, forged or billet as part of a deal. 
Beretta CX4 in 9mm with rails
FN SCAR 16, maybe 17
AK-47 rifles like Norinco Mak-90, Arsenal or Saiga converted model or not converted, I can convert myself easily.
Saiga 12 unconverted, may consider other calibers too if unconverted or converted if a good deal 
Beretta 92FS INOX, M9A1, 92A1, M9 and 92FS in this order, these are some of my favorites
Mossberg 930 SPX or 590A1, maybe 500 models, might look at a Remington 887 Tactical Nitro Mag. too.
XDM 5.25" or 4.5" in 9mm or .45ACP, will consider another XD Tactical 5" in .45ACP, bi-tone preferred.
1911 pistols
Quality higher powered optics in the 24x-32x range or similar for .300 Win Mag, .308 and .223 rifles.  A Nikon M-308 would be perfect for my AR-10
Maybe another Ruger GP100 .357 mag. 4" or 6" or other .357 mag. models, will consider .357 mag lever action, .44 Mag revolvers, maybe lever too.
Bolt actions in .223/5.56 and .308/7.62x51 must be rated for both like Savage.  Maybe a .22 Mag rifle too.
Ammo in the popular calibers: .22lr, .22 mag., 9mm, .40 S&W, .45ACP, .357 mag., .44 mag., .223/5.56, 7.62x39, .308/7.62x51, 7.62x54, .300 Win Mag., 12ga. in "00" & "000", same on ammo as firearms, I have plenty of everthing, but I will consider more ammo to make a deal, depending on the value you place on the ammo.

title: For Trade:  m91/30 1934 hex izy
postcontent:
Nagants in good enough shape to be salvaged were part of the soviets massive refurbishment program following ww2. The primary reasons behind the huge post war overhaul of large, obsolete rifle stockpiles were the anticipation of another impending world war, and the plan to call up seasoned veterans in defense of the motherland. Already familiar with their old mosin nagant rifles and revolvers, those veterans would likely have required very little new training and would easily and rapidly reintegrate into the red machine. 
With the development of newer semi auots that would have required extensive massive retraining, the important issue became of quick mobilization became apearant. However time passed and those great ww2 veterans eventually aged beyond the point of viability. While newer weapons took over the worlds battlefields, the stocks of long outdated ordnance were now imported to the USA. 

This is a pre war 1934 izzy manufacture m90/31 with hexagonal reciever with original russian laminate non refurbished stock. This rifles bore is stone mint shiny chromed out! "Have neer seen one like this" the weapon bears No refurbishment marks or other countrys arsenal markings! The metal has not a mark on it is stone mint! The magazine follower, action etc have no wear! Mint bore. All matching. No refurbishment marks from other countrys !!
This is a very early import that was sold wrapped in brown paper tied in twine. This rifle saw little to no action its entire life, maybe an officers or political gaurds weapon

The rifles antiquated lines, and historical signifigance is something to be sought after for years to come. This rifle was made well when an individuals workmanship was apreciated and one took pride in what they did. It also was a matter of national pride, a "we made it here" battle rifle.

This ammo comes from a local manufacturer,Vet-Made who we do big business with. We believe in keeping jobs and resources local, thus giving customers the best possible prices. Below is a little bit of information about this amazing company started by non only but United States veterans. 


ABOUT US 

        Vet-Made Ammunition, LLC was founded by U.S. Army Veterans Kenny Yates and Robert (Robbie) Atterholt, who combined have nearly 100 months in combat theaters. The two met serving in the same unit; and have completed multiple tours of combat service together.  Their service spans the United States Marine Corps, US Army, and the Tennessee Army National Guard. Kenny also served in Afghanistan as a civilian contractor.


ABOUT OUR EMPLOYEES

        The highest quality products must begin with the highest quality employees. For this reason, Vet-Made Ammunition, LLC exclusively hires only military veterans, or the immediate family members of deployed military personnel. Every aspect of our production facility and our processes are geared toward creating jobs for disabled veterans. Our goal is to enrich the lives of those who have served by providing meaningful employment and business opportunities.  

​

OUR MISSION

        Vet-Made Ammunition, LLC manufactures quality and affordable ammunition. In doing so, we strive to encourage and secure participation and future growth within all aspects of the shooting sports. 



*Featured price is on a cash basis, an additional charge will be applied only for CC over the phone*
